&lt;div&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;PDq2pG_selectionAnchorContainer&quot; data-start=&quot;97&quot; data-end=&quot;389&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong data-start=&quot;97&quot; data-end=&quot;242&quot;&gt;Are you a proven automotive Sales Manager who knows how to lead from the front, coach a high-performing team, and deliver consistent results?&lt;/strong&gt; Subaru Pacific is seeking an experienced Sales Manager to drive sales performance, develop top talent, and create an exceptional guest experience.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;394&quot; data-end=&quot;795&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;In this role, you will lead and motivate the sales team, oversee daily sales operations, and implement strategies that drive profitability and exceed performance goals. The ideal candidate has a strong background in automotive sales leadership, excels at coaching and developing teams, and is committed to delivering an exceptional guest experience while fostering a winning, customer-focused culture.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;394&quot; data-end=&quot;795&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;*Only candidates local to the South Bay/Los Angeles area with a reasonable commute will be considered*&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;The Sales Manager is responsible for optimizing sales and profitability while overseeing and managing the operations of our Sales department.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Develop and implement sales strategies to increase sales.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Hire, train and develop a team of Automotive Sales Consultants.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Direct and schedule the activities of department employees and monitor performance to ensure individual and department goals are achieved.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Maintain appropriate levels of customer service and client retention by resolving customer complaints or concerns immediately and appropriately.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Required:&lt;/strong&gt; Minimum 2 years of Automotive Sales Desk Manager experience leading a successful sales team within an Automotive Dealership setting&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Proven track record of achieving sales goals and driving dealership performance&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;High-energy, results-driven attitude with strong leadership and coaching skills&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Excellent communication and customer service abilities&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Proficiency in F&amp;amp;I processes and CDK software&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Valid driver’s license and acceptable driving record&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
